<body>
    <h1> How to make mac and cheesse </h1>
    <img src="../images/cheese.jpg" alt="noodles coated in cheese"
<div>
    <h3>The History</h3>
    <p>
        Mac and cheese, also known as macaroni and cheese, is a popular dish made with cooked macaroni pasta and a cheese sauce. 
        The origins of this dish can be traced back to Italy, where a similar dish called "maccheroni alla milanese" was created in the 14th century. 
    </p>
    <div>
        <h2>Ingridents</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 lb elbow macaroni</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons butter</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons flour</li>
            <li>2 cups milk, warmed</li>
            <li>1 -2 lb sharp cheddar cheese</li> 
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div> 
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Boil and drain macaroni per box instructions.</li>
            <li>Melt the butter in a skillet.</li>
            <li>Melt the butter in a skillet.</li>
            <li>Sprinkle in flour and stir until pasty.</li>
            <li>Whisk in warmed milk and let cook until thickened.</li>
            <li>Add cheese to sauce.</li>
            <li>Add sauce to pasta.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
